translated: Högberg, Knut Ragnar Natanael, vicar, Lane-Ryr, b. 8/4/93 in Solberga, Gothenburg and Bohuslän, son of vicar Lars Emanuel H. and Anna Gustava Svensson. Married in 1922 to Anna Cornér-Gornielius. Children: Erland b. 1938. He studied at Halmstad in 1911 and received a degree in theological philosophy from Lund in 1912, a degree in theology in 1914, passed the practical theological exam in 1915 and was ordained as a priest in the Gothenburg diocese in 1916. He served as a church assistant in Fänberg in 1918, vicar in Malmön in 1922, church assistant in Uddevalla in 1929 and vicar in Lane-Ryr since 1937. He was chairman of the school board, the poor relief board, the family assistance committee, the parish meeting, and the church council, and has been a member of the Gothenburg cathedral chapter since 1947.
